```

### 7. Smart Turn Index Synchronization

When toggling between Linear and Turn mode, preserve the user's position:

**Linear -> Turn**: Determine which turn contains `detail_event_index`. Walk the turns to find which one includes the current event index, set `turn_index` accordingly.

```rust
fn event_index_to_turn_index(turns: &[Turn], event_idx: usize) -> usize {
    for (ti, turn) in turns.iter().enumerate() {
        if turn.user_event_indices.contains(&event_idx)
            || turn.agent_event_indices.contains(&event_idx)
        {
            return ti;
        }
    }
    0
}
```

**Turn -> Linear**: Set `detail_event_index` to the first event of the current turn (first user event, or first agent event if no user events).

```rust
fn turn_index_to_event_index(turns: &[Turn], turn_idx: usize) -> usize {
    if let Some(turn) = turns.get(turn_idx) {
        turn.user_event_indices.first()
            .or(turn.agent_event_indices.first())
            .copied()
            .unwrap_or(0)
    } else {
        0
    }
}
```

### 8. Edge Cases

| Edge Case | Handling |
|-----------|----------|
| Session starts with agent events (no initial UserMessage) | Turn 0 has empty `user_event_indices`; left panel shows "(system preamble)" |
| All UserMessages filtered out (e.g., filter = Tools only) | Single turn with everything in agent panel, empty user panel showing "(filtered out)" |
| Very narrow terminal (< 80 chars) | Fall back to stacked layout (user on top, agent below) or show a warning. Check `area.width < 60` and use vertical split instead. |
| Session with only one user message | Single turn -- j/k does nothing |
| Turn with hundreds of tool calls | Agent panel shows condensed one-liners by default; PageDown scrolls; Enter expands |
| Consecutive collapse active | Works naturally since `extract_turns` operates on already-collapsed `DisplayEvent` list |
| `DisplayEvent::Collapsed` in agent panel | Render as a single line: "FileRead x5 collapsed" |
| `DisplayEvent::TaskSummary` in agent panel | Render as single line with task icon |

