### 2. Turn Extraction Algorithm

Add this as a method on `App` (or as a free function in `session_detail.rs`):

```rust
/// Extract conversational turns from the visible (filtered) event list.
/// A turn boundary occurs at each UserMessage event.
/// Events before the first UserMessage form "Turn 0" with an empty user side
/// (the preamble/system turn).
fn extract_turns(visible_events: &[DisplayEvent]) -> Vec<Turn> {
    let mut turns: Vec<Turn> = Vec::new();
    let mut current_user_indices: Vec<usize> = Vec::new();
    let mut current_agent_indices: Vec<usize> = Vec::new();
    let mut in_user_block = false;

    for (i, de) in visible_events.iter().enumerate() {
        let event = de.event();
        let is_user = matches!(event.event_type, EventType::UserMessage);

        if is_user {
            // If we have accumulated agent events, finalize the previous turn
            if !current_user_indices.is_empty() || !current_agent_indices.is_empty() {
                turns.push(build_turn(
                    visible_events,
                    &current_user_indices,
                    &current_agent_indices,
                ));
            }
            current_user_indices = vec![i];
            current_agent_indices = Vec::new();
            in_user_block = true;
        } else if in_user_block && matches!(event.event_type, EventType::SystemMessage) {
            // System messages right after user message stay in user column
            current_user_indices.push(i);
        } else {
            in_user_block = false;
            current_agent_indices.push(i);
        }
    }

    // Finalize the last turn
    if !current_user_indices.is_empty() || !current_agent_indices.is_empty() {
        turns.push(build_turn(
            visible_events,
            &current_user_indices,
            &current_agent_indices,
        ));
    }

    turns
}
```

**Key design decisions:**

- **Preamble handling**: If the session starts with agent/system events before any `UserMessage`, those form Turn 0 with an empty left panel. The left panel shows "(system preamble)" or similar placeholder text.
- **Filter interaction**: Turns are extracted from the **already-filtered** `DisplayEvent` list, so filters (1-6 keys) naturally apply. If a filter hides all UserMessages, the entire session collapses into a single turn with an empty user panel.
- **Recomputation**: Turns are recomputed on each render call (they are cheap index vectors). No caching needed since the visible event list is already recomputed each frame.

